Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report. Based on my thorough exploration, here's what I found:

## Comprehensive Analysis: AI Provider Package Structure in Vercel AI SDK

I've completed a very thorough exploration of three major AI provider packages in the Vercel AI SDK monorepo. Here's the detailed structure and patterns:

---

## 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

All provider packages follow an identical structure:

```
packages/{provider}/
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── tsconfig.build.json
├── tsup.config.ts
├── turbo.json
├── internal.d.ts
├── vitest.node.config.js
├── vitest.edge.config.js
├── CHANGELOG.md
├── README.md
└── src/
    ├── index.ts                         (main exports)
    ├── version.ts
    ├── {provider}-provider.ts            (factory + interface)
    ├── {provider}-error.ts
    ├── {provider}-tools.ts
    ├── internal/
    │   └── index.ts                     (internal exports)
    └── {model-types}/
        ├── {provider}-{type}-language-model.ts
        ├── {provider}-{type}-options.ts
        └── (tests & fixtures)
```

**Example for OpenAI:**
- `src/chat/` (chat language models)
- `src/completion/` (completion models)
- `src/embedding/` (embedding models)
- `src/image/` (image generation)
- `src/responses/` (responses API)
- `src/speech/` (text-to-speech)
- `src/transcription/` (audio transcription)
- `src/tool/` (specialized tools like file-search, code-interpreter)

---

## 2. PACKAGE.JSON PATTERNS

All providers use **identical package.json structure**:

```json
{
  "name": "@ai-sdk/{provider}",
  "version": "3.x.x",
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "docs/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__",
    "CHANGELOG.md",
    "README.md",
    "internal.d.ts"
  ],
  "exports": {
    "./package.json": "./package.json",
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    },
    "./internal": {
      "types": "./dist/internal/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/internal/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/internal/index.js"
    }
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/provider": "workspace:*",
    "@ai-sdk/provider-utils": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "zod": "^3.25.76 || ^4.1.8"
  },
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=18"
  },
  "publishConfig": {
    "access": "public"
  }
}
```

**Key fields:**
- Dual CJS/ESM exports
- Two export points: main API (`.`) and `./internal` (for advanced use)
- Always depends on `@ai-sdk/provider` and `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`
- Always has `zod` as peer dependency

---

## 3. TSCONFIG PATTERNS

All providers use the **same minimal tsconfig.json**:

```json
{
  "extends": "./node_modules/@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "exclude": [
    "dist",
    "build",
    "node_modules",
    "tsup.config.ts",
    "internal.d.ts"
  ],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../provider" },
    { "path": "../provider-utils" }
  ]
}
```

**tsconfig.build.json** disables composite for builds:
```json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": false
  }
}
```

---

## 4. BUILD CONFIGURATION (tsup.config.ts)

All providers use **two build entries** via tsup:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'tsup';

export default defineConfig([
  {
    entry: ['src/index.ts'],
    format: ['cjs', 'esm'],
    dts: true,
    sourcemap: true,
    define: {
      __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(version),
    },
  },
  {
    entry: ['src/internal/index.ts'],
    outDir: 'dist/internal',
    format: ['cjs', 'esm'],
    dts: true,
    sourcemap: true,
    define: {
      __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(version),
    },
  },
]);
```

**Key points:**
- Builds both main entry and internal entry separately
- Both output CJS + ESM
- Both generate TypeScript declarations
- Both include source maps

---

## 5. EXPORTS PATTERN (src/index.ts)

### OpenAI (src/index.ts):
```typescript
export { createOpenAI, openai } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAIProvider, OpenAIProviderSettings } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAILanguageModelChatOptions } from './chat/openai-chat-options';
export type { OpenAILanguageModelCompletionOptions } from './completion/openai-completion-options';
export type { OpenAIEmbeddingModelOptions } from './embedding/openai-embedding-options';
export type { OpenAISpeechModelOptions } from './speech/openai-speech-options';
export type { OpenAITranscriptionModelOptions } from './transcription/openai-transcription-options';
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

### Google (src/index.ts):
```typescript
export type { GoogleErrorData } from './google-error';
export type { GoogleLanguageModelOptions } from './google-generative-ai-options';
export type { GoogleImageModelOptions } from './google-generative-ai-image-model';
export type { GoogleEmbeddingModelOptions } from './google-generative-ai-embedding-options';
export { createGoogleGenerativeAI, google } from './google-provider';
export type { GoogleGenerativeAIProvider, GoogleGenerativeAIProviderSettings } from './google-provider';
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

### Anthropic (src/index.ts):
```typescript
export type { AnthropicMessageMetadata, AnthropicUsageIteration } from './anthropic-message-metadata';
export type { AnthropicLanguageModelOptions } from './anthropic-messages-options';
export { anthropic, createAnthropic } from './anthropic-provider';
export type { AnthropicProvider, AnthropicProviderSettings } from './anthropic-provider';
export { forwardAnthropicContainerIdFromLastStep } from './forward-anthropic-container-id-from-last-step';
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

**Pattern:**
- Always exports a factory function (`create{Provider}`)
- Always exports a default instance (lowercase, e.g., `openai`, `google`, `anthropic`)
- Exports provider interface and settings interface
- Exports model-specific options types
- Exports VERSION constant

---

## 6. INTERNAL EXPORTS (src/internal/index.ts)

### OpenAI:
```typescript
export * from '../chat/openai-chat-language-model';
export * from '../chat/openai-chat-options';
export * from '../completion/openai-completion-language-model';
export * from '../embedding/openai-embedding-model';
export * from '../image/openai-image-model';
export * from '../responses/openai-responses-language-model';
export * from '../tool/apply-patch';
export * from '../tool/code-interpreter';
export * from '../tool/file-search';
```

### Google:
```typescript
export * from '../google-generative-ai-language-model';
export { googleTools } from '../google-tools';
export type { GoogleGenerativeAIModelId } from '../google-generative-ai-options';
```

**Purpose:** Exposes internal implementation classes for advanced use cases and custom integrations.

---

## 7. internal.d.ts FILE

All providers have identical **internal.d.ts**:
```typescript
export * from './dist/internal';
```

This allows TypeScript ambient module declaration to re-export internal types.

---

## 8. PROVIDER FACTORY FUNCTION PATTERN

### OpenAI (openai-provider.ts):

```typescript
export interface OpenAIProvider extends ProviderV3 {
  (modelId: OpenAIResponsesModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  languageModel(modelId: OpenAIResponsesModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  chat(modelId: OpenAIChatModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  completion(modelId: OpenAICompletionModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  embedding(modelId: OpenAIEmbeddingModelId): EmbeddingModelV3;
  image(modelId: OpenAIImageModelId): ImageModelV3;
  transcription(modelId: OpenAITranscriptionModelId): TranscriptionModelV3;
  speech(modelId: OpenAISpeechModelId): SpeechModelV3;
  tools: typeof openaiTools;
}

export interface OpenAIProviderSettings {
  baseURL?: string;
  apiKey?: string;
  organization?: string;
  project?: string;
  headers?: Record<string, string>;
  name?: string;
  fetch?: FetchFunction;
}

export function createOpenAI(options: OpenAIProviderSettings = {}): OpenAIProvider {
  const baseURL = withoutTrailingSlash(loadOptionalSetting({...})) ?? 'https://api.openai.com/v1';
  const providerName = options.name ?? 'openai';

  const getHeaders = () => withUserAgentSuffix(
    {
      Authorization: `Bearer ${loadApiKey({...})}`,
      'OpenAI-Organization': options.organization,
      'OpenAI-Project': options.project,
      ...options.headers,
    },
    `ai-sdk/openai/${VERSION}`,
  );

  const createChatModel = (modelId) => 
    new OpenAIChatLanguageModel(modelId, {
      provider: `${providerName}.chat`,
      url: ({ path }) => `${baseURL}${path}`,
      headers: getHeaders,
      fetch: options.fetch,
    });

  // ...similar for other model types...

  const provider = function (modelId) {
    if (new.target) {
      throw new Error('The OpenAI model function cannot be called with the new keyword.');
    }
    return createLanguageModel(modelId);
  };

  provider.specificationVersion = 'v3' as const;
  provider.languageModel = createLanguageModel;
  provider.chat = createChatModel;
  provider.embedding = createEmbeddingModel;
  provider.image = createImageModel;
  provider.transcription = createTranscriptionModel;
  provider.speech = createSpeechModel;
  provider.tools = openaiTools;

  return provider as OpenAIProvider;
}

export const openai = createOpenAI();
```

### Google (google-provider.ts):

```typescript
export interface GoogleGenerativeAIProvider extends ProviderV3 {
  (modelId: GoogleGenerativeAIModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  languageModel(modelId: GoogleGenerativeAIModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  chat(modelId: GoogleGenerativeAIModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  image(modelId: GoogleGenerativeAIImageModelId, settings?: GoogleGenerativeAIImageSettings): ImageModelV3;
  embedding(modelId: GoogleGenerativeAIEmbeddingModelId): EmbeddingModelV3;
  video(modelId: GoogleGenerativeAIVideoModelId): Experimental_VideoModelV3;
